The paper discusses statistical inference and exploration strategies for reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with control and optimization problems, which are relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves numerical experiments and data analysis, which are related to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
